<HEADLINE> Suzhou Industrial Park Attracts Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, December 26 (Xinhua) - The Suzhou Industrial Park in
east China's Jiangsu Province has attracted over 3.6 billion US
dollars in foreign funding since its establishment a short three
years ago.
</P>
<P>
The park has used Singaporean experience in its construction,
environmental protection, and development plans, according to
economists attending a Friday symposium in Suzhou sponsored by the
Special Economic Zones Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The average investment for infrastructure construction for the
eight square kilometers completed during the first construction
phase stood at 380 million yuan (45 million US dollars) per sq.m.,
some 2.39 times the average for 32 similar projects in China.
</P>
<P>
The park, a Sino-Singaporean joint venture, will contribute to
economic cooperation between the two countries and to the
modernization of Chinese industry, according to Ge Hongsheng,
director of the Special Economic Zones Office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
