<HEADLINE> Road Death Toll Climbs to 539 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The death toll on South
Africa's roads since December 1 had climbed to 539 by Friday
morning, the traffic authorities said.
</P>
<P>
Of these 180 were pedestrians, 142 were drivers and 217
passengers, "Arrive Alive Campaign" spokesman Joshua Raborifi
said.
</P>
<P>
Most accidents were caused by high speed and pedestrian
jay-walking, he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 people died in road accidents in the Christmas
season last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
