<HEADLINE> 22 Traffic Accidents in Zambia on Christmas Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Twenty two road traffic
accidents were reported to the police throughout Zambia on
Christmas Day, leaving one person killed and five injured, Zambia
News Agency ZANA reported today.
</P>
<P>
ZANA quoted a police spokesman as saying that the number of
accidents reported this Christmas almost doubles the figure of
last year which was 12 with two persons killed and three injured.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, two cars were grabbed by armed robbers and
another car was stolen, said the spokesman, adding that no
arrests have been made in connection with the three cars.
</P>
<P>
Christmas is a big occasion in this Christian country. There
used to be many celebrating parties sponsored by the government
agencies in the past years.
</P>
<P>
However, there were no signs to show that parties on council
accounts were held and people consider it as a move to fight
against corruption.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the Zambian government announced that
apart from privately arranged parties, no council-sponsored
Christmas parties shall be allowed this year and the same applies
to new year festivals. The offenders will be surcharged or
penalized, said the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
