<HEADLINE> 4 Killed in Road Accident North of Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Four passengers were
instantly killed and 32 others injured when a public transport
bus skidded and overturned 42 kilometers north of Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
According to local police, the bus which was carrying 63
passengers was overturned last Tuesday when it was on its way
from Addis Ababa to Drbre-Tabor, about 400 km north of Addis.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus is still at large and the police is now
investigating the accident. 
