<HEADLINE> Iraq: US Preparing Attacks on Its Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 26 (Xinhua)-- There are clear signs that the
United States is making preparations for attacks on Iraqi
presidential palaces, an official Iraqi spokesman warned today
after a cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
At the cabinet meeting, chaired by Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein, the development of the situation, U.S. attempt to commit
aggression against Iraq and the lifting of the U.N. sanctions were
discussed, the official Iraqi news agency INA reported.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the United States is still
manipulating the United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) on
eliminating Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, which have
conducted thousands of visits to Iraqi sites in the past six and
a half years.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. knows very well that Iraq has no prohibited weapons,
the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
However, the United States sticks to their lies and insists
that chemical and biological weapons are hidden in the
presidential palaces, said the spokesman, adding that the U.S. is
making preparations for taking military actions against these
palaces.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman warned that the U.S. should know that its
anti-Iraq attempt will not succeed, saying that Iraq is highly
vigilant against any possible U.S. aggressions.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has been refusing to grant access to U.N. arms inspectors
to the presidential sites, which Iraq regards as symbols of its
sovereignty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
