<DOCNO> XIE19971227.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia's Inter-Party Dialog to Be Held Ahead of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Co-chairman of the inter-party
talks Micheal Sata announced here today that the proposed
inter-party dialog will be held in Livingstone, southern Zambia,
on December 30 and 31 instead of planned January 10 next year.
</P>
<P>
The government minister without portfolio made the
announcement one day after the United National Independence Party
(UNIP) led by former president Kenneth Kaunda announced its
withdrawal from the inter-party dialog.
</P>
<P>
Sata also appointed one official of the opposition Zambia
Democratic Congress (ZDC) as co-chairman to replace Mainza Chona,
who quitted from his post after UNIP pulled out of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Chona, UNIP Central Committee member, and Sata were chosen
co-chairmen earlier this month when a preliminary meeting of the
inter-party talks was held.
</P>
<P>
UNIP pulled out of the talks after Kaunda was arrested by
police early Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three more parties joined in UNIP today by pulling
out of the talks in protest against Kaunda's arrest.
</P>
<P>
The three parties are the National Democratic Party (NDP), the
National Patriotic Alliance and Agenda for Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda returned home on Monday after a marathon overseas trip,
which took him to India, South Africa, Zimbabwe, the United
States and Britain among other countries.
</P>
<P>
He went abroad on the eve of the October 28 abortive coup in
Zambia to seek international pressure on the government.
</P>
<P>
After the coup some reports said Kaunda would not return home
for fear of being arrested and would instead seek asylum abroad
but he denied the reports.
</P>
<P>
At the preliminary meeting held early this month 31 parties
drew an agenda for the inter-party dialog. The agenda includes
most contentious issues like constitution, electoral process and
voters' register and fresh registration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
