<HEADLINE> 9 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Turkish government troops
today killed nine rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK) in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
