<HEADLINE> Defending Champion Loses Opener in Women's Volleyball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Shanghai
was defeated by newly-promoted Tianjin 3-0, the biggest and only
upset as the China's volleyball leagues started off on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
On their home turf, the Shanghai women rushed to an early lead
of 14-9 in the first set through pierce attacks and solid blocks.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Tianjin, which was promoted to the league from division B,
proved to be hard nut for the reigning champions by ralling back
to win seven points in a row to stun the home fans.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin kept its winning trend through fast attacks and
varified tactics to take the second set 15-12.
</P>
<P>
In the third set, Shanghai squandered its 10-6 lead with a
string of unforced errors before Tianjin achieved its away win for
the day's upset, sealing the competition as ace spiker Lu Chao
displayed her top-class calibre on the court.
</P>
<P>
Cai Bin, coach of Shanghai, blamed his disciples for failure to
adjust for the league on time as defending champions mentally
which resulted in errors in their techniques.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the Jiangsu women spikers won their opener
against Sichuan, which was tougher than what the 3-0 scoreboard
suggested.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, runner-up in last season, fielded in the same line-up
including national players Sun Yue, Qu Aihua and Li Julan, while
Sichuan, formed prior to the Eighth National Games in October,
featured the majority of debutants in its roster.
</P>
<P>
However, Sichuan surged ahead 12-9 in the first set before
Jiangsu rallied back to overturn the trend by winning the last six
points in a row under the cheers from thousands of home fans.
</P>
<P>
The home squad continued its dominance in the second set for a
comfortable lead of 12-9 before the Sichuan women capitulized upon
two faults for 12-11.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the home team stopped the visitors from scoring any
more points before sealing the competition 15-12, 15-11 and 15-9.
</P>
<P>
In other first round women's matches, two other teams exploited
their home advantages as Zhejiang beat Fujian 15-1, 15-5, 15-11
and the Liberation Army romped Liaoning 15-4, 15-8, 15-7.
</P>
<P>
The men's volleyball league also started on Saturday with all
four home teams winning their openers.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Sichuan defeated visiting Shanghai 15-7,
15-13, 15-13, Zhejiang outscored Henan 16-14, 15-8, 15-9, Liaoning
savored its victory against Hubei 15-12, 15-2, 15-9 while Jiangsu
whitewashed Beijing 15-5, 15-10, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
Both the men's and women's volleyball leagues feature an
identical eight teams competiting in the 28-round tournaments with
two games for each squad on every Saturday and Sunday in 14
weeks which runs to April 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
