<HEADLINE> New Killings of Civilians Reported in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven civilians were
killed from Thursday night till Friday morning in a village in
Tiaret, 200 kilometers southwest of the Algerian capital of
Algiers, reports from Algeria said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The latest killings took place three days after 48 people were
killed in two other villages in the same region.
</P>
<P>
Among the victims was a 21-day-old baby.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian army is launching a new offensive against Islamic
militants and killed several dozen extremists.
</P>
<P>
Security forces have surrounded an armed group of extremists on
the southeast outskirt of Algiers, while the army destroyed a
workshop producing explosives in Oran, western Algeria.
</P>
<P>
General Kamel Abderrahmane, chief of the Second Military Region
based in Oran, had asked civilians living in villages to take up
arms or take shelter in big cities after the two massacres took
place in Tiaret.
</P>
<P>
Islamic extremists have increased their attacks as the Muslim
fasting month of Ramadan is approaching, causing tension among
Algerians about a violence-ridden Ramadan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
