<HEADLINE> Wong Kam Po Wins 1st Stage in Tour of South China Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's top cyclist and
defending champion Wong Kam Po won the opening stage of the six
stages, 426-km Second Tour of South China Sea Cycling Race here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Wong, winner of the men's 180 km road race at China's National
Games in October this year, is competing in Hong Kong Team A in
the Tour.
</P>
<P>
He covered the 15-km time-trial stage on Saturday at the Bride
Pool Road, Tai Po, in a title-winning time of 22 minutes 28.17
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Wong was followed by Yamaguchi Shuji of Hong Kong's CWX Jian Li
Bao Team in 22:55.75 and Shuji's teammate Eric Sutherland in
23:12.36.
</P>
<P>
Fuzino Tomokuzu from Japan's Inoac-Deki Shimano Team, winner of
this year's Tour of Okinawa, finished fourth and China's Pan
Guangchun, member of the title-winning Liaoning provincial team at
this year's National Games in Shanghai, was fifth in the opening
stage on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
China's top racer Tang Xuezhong, multiple winner at Asian
Games, Asian championships and national championships, suffered a
blown tire some six kilometers into the stage and finished a
disappointing 34th.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Team A won the team title for the stage with a time
of 45.52 seconds, followed by Japan Inoac-Deki Shimano in 46.43,
China in 47.35, Mongolia in 48.21, and Kaohsiung of Chinese Taipei
in 48.38.
</P>
<P>
The second stage on Sunday is a 67.5 km, 25 laps road race at
Yuen Long Industrial Estate in the northern part of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Tour then moves to the South China city of Zhuhai for two
more stages there next Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The six-day Tour closes with another two stages in Macao, on
Wednesday and Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
