<HEADLINE> Wholesale Seafood Market Opens in Nanning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The largest local wholesale
seafood market of its kind opened today in the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, south China.
</P>
<P>
The downtown Nanning market complex features restaurants,
department stores, hotels and banks, in addition to facilities
focusing on seafood transportation and processing.
</P>
<P>
Annual sales of seafood and freshwater fish are expected to
reach 20,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's output of aquatic products has grown rapidly in
recent years, with projections for 1997 calling a 19 percent
increase on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Nanning is considered to be an ideal seafood wholesale and
trade center linking Guangdong, Hong Kong, Macao and countries in
Southeast Asia.  
</P>
