<HEADLINE> Record Offshore Crude Oil Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The China National Offshore
Oil Corp (CNOOC) expects to pump a record 16.2 million tons of
crude oil and four billion cu.m. of natural gas (four million tons
of oil) in 1997.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC President Wang Yan said today that the country has
recorded an astonishing 80 percent success ratio for offshore
wildcat drilling, with additional proven reserves for 1997
standing at 176 million tons of oil and 8.6 billion cu.m. of gas.
</P>
<P>
"Nineteen operational offshore oil and gas fields are
profitable," said Wang. He added that CNOOC projects that this
year's total sales and net profits will hit 14.8 billion yuan and
3.3 billion yuan respectively.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC signed 131 oil contracts and agreements with 67 oil
companies from 18 countries and regions by the end of 1997, with
total foreign investments standing at 6.4 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The corporation warmly welcomes foreign cooperation in oil and
gas exploration in the South China Sea, East China Sea and
Yellow Sea. 
</P>
