<HEADLINE> Le Pen Threatens Retaliation Against Overseas Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Le Pen, president of the French
rightest National Front, threatened Saturday to retaliate against
the overseas territories of France after he was rounded up by
protesters in Martinique, a Caribbean island ruled by France.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said that Le Pen met with a protest by some 50
militants of the independence movement of Martinique at the
airport of Fort-de-France, where he made a stopover before flying
to Porto-Rico for a visit.
</P>
<P>
The protesters attacked Le Pen for his remarks about "racial
inequality" and the gas chamber of Nazi death camps, which he
described as "a point of detail in the history of World War II."
</P>
<P>
"Think it over well that I am a deputy of the European
Parliament and that I know how to take into account this attitude
in the discussions which will involve the interests of these
islands (at the parliament)," said Le Pen.
</P>
<P>
The protest took place one day after a court in Nanterre near
Paris condemned Le Pen for his remarks on gas chambers, which he
made on December 5 in Germany. 
</P>
