registered gains Friday, as investors appeared hopeful that the
latest Korean bailout package will prevent a wider financial
crisis. However, in Japan, where investors raised new questions
about the Tokyo government's handling of its own shaky financial
system, stock prices fell 3.25 percent even as the finance
minister declared his nation's crisis at an end.
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin took a small step toward
resolving one of post-Soviet Russia's most intractable conflicts
Friday, convening a Kremlin round table on land reform that
pledged to hammer out a compromise land code over the next three
months. 
