<HEADLINE> Sudanese Warplane Shot Down Near Uganda-Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A Sudanese war plane has been
shot down near the Uganda-Sudan border, The New Vision reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The plane was hovering over Bibia and Kilak counties in the
northern district of Gulu before the incident, military sources
in the north claimed.
</P>
<P>
The incident coincided with an abortive attack by a combined
forces of Sudanese government army and Ugandan rebels of the
Lord's Resistance Army (LRA) on Sudanese People's Liberation Army
(SPLA) positions in southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
It was the SPLA which shot down the plane, it is said.
</P>
<P>
SPLA is a rebel group operating in southern Sudan. Uganda and
Sudan have been blaming each other for supporting the rebels in
the other country.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth time a Sudanese plane was downed in the
Uganda-Sudan border areas this year.
</P>
<P>
Brigadier James Kazini, commander of the fourth division of
Ugandan army, has confirmed the incident. 
</P>
