<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lock System on China's Biggest Canal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 27 (Xinhua) - China has constructed another
lock system on the country's largest canal between Beijing and
Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The lock system was constructed in the Liushan Section of the
the Grand Canal, near the city of Pizhou in northern Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The lock, 230 meters by 23 meters by five meters deep, has an
annual handling capacity of 21 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Rapid economic development has increased the annual volume of
transport on the Grand Canal through northern Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
The new lock system is expected to ease congestion on the
canal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
