<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-27 13:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan's FM Arrives in Saudi Arabia for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's Minister of state
for Foreign Affairs Fayez Tarawneh arrived in Saudi Arabia today
to deliver a message from King Hussein to Saudi King Fahd on the
stalled Middle East Peace process and its negative implications
on peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Well-informed diplomatic sources were quoted by Kuwait News
Agency as saying that the letter also carries fresh ideas on means
of fostering relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Tarawneh is expected to deliver the
message to King Fahd later today and confer with Saudi Crown
Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Saudi Arabia, Rarawneh would also hold
talks with Saudi leaders on bilateral ties, regional situations,
the Middle East peace process and the Islamic summit held in Iran
recently, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They said the two countries share the same view regarding the
Middle East peace process which is based on the principle of
land-for-peace and U.N. resolutions on the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Amman and Riyadh hold the Israeli government fully
responsible for the current stalemate in the peace process
and assert that continuing its arrogant policy will only
complicate matters and threaten to undermine the whole peace
process.
</P>
<P>
The visit follows the official visit to Saudi Arabia by
Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan in September.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Saudi Arabia and Jordan have been improving
in recent years after several years' strain following the Gulf
War when Amman and Riyadh were on opposite sides.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia is Jordan's second largest trading partner after
Iraq. In 1996, Jordan exported about 184 million U.S. dollars
worth of goods to Saudi Arabia compared to 99 million U.S.
dollars in 1995, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Under a trade protocol, the two countries are expected to
set up a free trade zone by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's King Hussein visited Saudi Arabia early this year for
the first time in six years and held talks with Fahd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
