<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Province on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province is currently offering the "Golden Pigeon Program," a
program which helps people, especially foreigners, use the
Internest to learn more about the province.
</P>
<P>
An average of one million surfers have visited the Internet on a
monthly basis since June, with the vast majority of surfers coming
from the United States and West Europe.
</P>
<P>
Between July-November this year, more than 1.08 million people
surfed the web for information related to Hangzhou, the provincial
capital and a well-known scenic city.
</P>
<P>
The web page, operated by the Zhejiang Provincial Association
for Overseas Cultural Exchanges, was established in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
Officials noted that Zhejiang will offer practical and efficient
updated information related to detailed introductions to
investment projects in the province, as well as on major tourism
sites and activities designed to attract overseas investors and
advance the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Since the end of November, the "Golden Pigeon Program" has
received 3,744 electronic messages from 50 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
More than half of total contacts have been related to
investment and trade, with numerous local enterprises operating
online systems receiving direct contacts from overseas companies
concerning business ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
