<HEADLINE> Nigeria Loses 70 Percent Farm Produce to Pests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- About 70 percent of Nigeria's
agricultural produce are being destroyed by pests, according to
the Pest Control Association of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The destruction is not quantifiable as it is enormous in
monetary value and also amounts to a waste of man-hour as well as
starvation, said Kayode Odogbolu, president of the association,
quoted by the New Nigerian paper today.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there would be abundant food for the populace at
low prices if pests were effectively controlled, the president
promised to reinforce the efforts to fight the menace.
</P>
<P>
The association will continue to organize workshops to
peasants in the north, the country's agricultural production
base, to educate them on the application of chemicals on their
farm products.
</P>
<P>
Authorities concerned have taken measures to ensure the
importation of the right chemicals for pest control, reported the
official newspaper. 
