<HEADLINE> Vip Cells Expected in Nigerian Prisons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Nigeria Prisons Service has
planned to build very important persons (vips) cells for
convicted high-profile persons in some prisons in the country.
</P>
<P>
Vip cells would secure the vip inmates from the unpredicatable
onslaught of hardened criminals in ordinary cells, the Guardian
newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The prison authorities have proposed an increase in its budget
for the coming year, which is awaiting approval by the
provisional ruling council, the highest policy making body of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Also under scrutiny in the on-going budgetary process at the
finance ministry is a proposal to increase the inmates' food
ration from 50 Naira per head a day to 100 Naira (about 1.25 U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Inmates population in Nigerian prisons is estimated at about
50,000, with awaiting for trial persons accounting for 60
percent.
</P>
<P>
To provide better conditions for inmates, renovation work on
some prisons has reached advanced stage and are billed for
completion next year.
</P>
<P>
Part of the work includes expansion of farm centers to train
inmates in modern farming methods, that of workshops, provision
of sewage and potable water, building of prison schools and
hospitals. 
</P>
