<HEADLINE> Good Working Ties Forged Between HKSARG, MFA Office in Handling External Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Regional Government (HKSARG) has, since July 1,
established contacts and frequent communications with the
Commissioner's Office of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs
(MFA Office) in handling external affairs of the HKSAR, the HKSARG
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Through actual experience, we have established a good and
trusting relationship with the MFA Office," a spokesman from the
Constitutional Affairs Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
He was responding to press inquiries on remarks made
by Commissioner Ma Yuzhen in an earlier exclusive interview with
Xinhua, during which Ma briefed the news agency on the full
support and assistance given by his office to the HKSARG in the
past six months in handling external affairs on its own with due
authorization.
</P>
<P>
"As Commissioner Ma said, the MFA Office and HKSARG share the
common objectives of upholding sovereignty and fostering the
long-term stability and prosperity of Hong Kong. Both parties are
committed to work in strict accordance with the Basic Law and to
ensure the full implementation of the principle of 'One Country,
Two Systems'," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the relevant provisions of the Basic Law,
the HKSARG has, in the past six months, signed bilateral
agreements in various fields with foreign countries, and
participated actively in international organizations and
activities, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"We have, as before, been fully accepted and supported by our
partners in the international community," he noted.
</P>
<P>
During the period from July 1 to November 30, representatives
from the HKSARG participated as members of the People's Republic
of China delegation in more than 20 international conferences,
most of which were in the fields of communication, civil aviation,
etc., he continued.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out: "The fact that expatriate civil servants have
also taken part as members of the PRC delegation in attending
international conferences clearly demonstrates that the principle
of 'One Country, Two Systems' is being fully implemented in the
HKSAR."
</P>
<P>
In addition, HKSARG representatives also participated in more
than 200 international conferences "on our own" using the name
"Hong Kong, China", he continued.
</P>
<P>
The Central People's Government (CPG) formally announced on
November 22 that reports on the implementation of the
International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights (ICCPR) and
the International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights
(ICESCR) in the HKSAR would be submitted to the relevant treaty
monitoring bodies (TMBs) of the United Nations so that TMBs and
the international society will have a better understanding of the
human rights situation in the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
This arrangement not only reflects the determination of the CPG
to fully implement the principle of "One Country, Two Systems" but
also demonstrates the CPG's willingness to handle the matters
relating the HKSAR in a flexible way so as to take into account
the practical needs of the HKSAR, the spokesman noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the HKSARG is grateful for the support given by
the CPG and the assistance rendered by the MFA Office. "We will
continue to cooperate closely with the MFA Office and to further
develop and strengthen our working relationship," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
