<HEADLINE> Lithuania Announces Presidential Election Result </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Neither of the seven candidates
gained over 50 percent of votes in the first round of Lithuania's
presidential elections on December 21, the Main Electoral
Commission said.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported from Vilnius, capital of
Lithuania, that 71.77 percent of voters cast ballots.
</P>
<P>
Former prosecutor of Lithuania lawyer Arturas Paulauskas, 44,
of left-centrist view, gained 44.73 percent of votes, while
71-year-old right-centrist Valdas Adamkus won 27.56 percent of
votes.
</P>
<P>
The third place was occupied by the rightists' leader,
parliament speaker Vitautas Landsbergis, who gained 15.73 percent
of votes.
</P>
<P>
Paulauskas and Landsbergis will take part in the second round
of the elections on January 4, 1998. 
