quarter the aid subsidized for regional development, as the European
Union (EU) is preparing for a new sharing of financial aid among EU
countries after the enlargement of the union to central and eastern
European countries. Some opposition politicians are worried that the
French government would obey Brussels, while others are mobilizing
in the regions which are the primary beneficiaries of EU aid, such
as Auvergne and Limousin.
</P>
<P>
