<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Operating Effectively in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign banks operating in
Vietnam mobilized over 21 trillion Vietnamese dong (1.75 billion
U.S. dollars) in the last 10 months, reported Vietnam News Agency
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This accounts for 19.2 percent of the total amount mobilized by
the banking system in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The combined value of loans issued by foreign banks hit over
19 trillion dong (1.58 billion dollars) in the first ten months of
this year, up 4.7 percent compared to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign banks' representative offices in Vietnam have served as
bridges between their banks and foreign investors doing business
in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
And they have signed credit agreements worth nearly 2 billion
dollars with local businesses and banks. Of the total amount, 620
million dollars have been disbursed to date.
</P>
<P>
There are 24 foreign bank branches, four joint-venture banks,
three finance leasing companies and 76 foreign bank representative
offices operating in Vietnam. 
</P>
