<HEADLINE> Northeast China Port City Attracting More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a port city of
northeast China's Liaoning Province, has received 17.2 million
tourists this year, including 200,000 tourists from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, situated at the southern tip of the Liaodong Peninsula
where the Bohai and the Yellow seas meet, has a string of
beautiful islands, scenic spots, beaches and seashore resorts
along its coastline.
</P>
<P>
The city has organized a host of programs, including an annual
garment festival, Bingyu Fireworks and Ice Lantern Festival, to
advance development of tourism industry, Zhang Hongan, director of
the Dalian City Tourism Administration, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
More specialized tourist programs, such as "be a Dalian
resident for one day", "become a farmer in Dalian for one day",
are also being considered, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 150 tourist hotels, of which, 65 are of star
classification. The top ones are the Shangri-La Dalian Hotel,
which started business early this month, and the Ruruma Hotel.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, with a history of 100 years, is also a major
shipbuilding base in China as well as the country's biggest diesel
engine manufacturing center. It is also the third largest port in
China, with 4,300 cargo ship calling there each year.
</P>
<P>
The city, where high technology begins to take root, has
planned to become a center of trade, banking, tourism and
information in northeast Asia over the next 20 years. Moreover, it
will be turned into an important international traffic hub and an
industrial base propped up by advanced technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
