<HEADLINE> Holiday Accidents Claim 20 Lives in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Twenty Zimbabweans, including
two babies, were killed and 106 others injured in 120 road
accidents reported throughout the country on Christmas Eve and
Christmas Day, The Herald daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Police press and public relations officer Joe Manyakaidze was
quoted as saying that a total of 101 crashes were reported on
Christmas Day during which 74 people were injured.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to all motorists and road users to help preserve
life on the roads by exercising caution.
</P>
<P>
"The carnage on our roads can only be effectively reduced if
we all play our part," Manyakaidze noted.
</P>
<P>
The figures released so far suggest that the total number of
reported accidents this year is less than last year's 201 over
the same period.
</P>
<P>
Christmas Day was relatively quiet throughout the country,
with police attributing this to a reduction on the volume of
traffic on the roads. The capital Harare recorded an unusually
low number of crashes which stood at 31 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As is the case over most holidays, drunken driving, speeding,
fatigue, and general lack of courtesy were the major cause of
accidents on the part of motorists, said the police officer.
</P>
