<HEADLINE> Overseas Sri Lankan Workers' Remittances on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankans working abroad
have remitted 633 million U.S. dollars of foreign exchange to
their home country during the first three quarters this year, the
Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment (SLBFE) said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The bureau predicted that total remittances for 1997 will reach
833 million dollars. Last year the remittances stood at 767
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the increase in foreign employment earnings to
the implementation of a policy which requires overseas job seekers
to register with the bureau before proceeding abroad.
</P>
<P>
Job seekers need to provide proper training certificates so as
to obtain a special security stamp from the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The stamp indicates that the holder has fulfilled requirements
of the SLBFE and he or she is allowed to obtain an air ticket.
</P>
<P>
Currently there are about one million Sri Lankans working
abroad, of which 60 to 70 percent are in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The SLBFE plans to increase the number of foreign employment
opportunities for locals by 20 percent by the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
