<HEADLINE> China's New Goal for Oil, Gas Production Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The China National Offshore
Oil Corp (CNOOC) is expected to produce 16.2 million tons of oil
and four billion cu m of natural gas (equivalent to four million
tons of oil ) this year.
</P>
<P>
The oil and gas output will be two million tons equivalent more
than that of last year, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang Yan, president of the corporation, his
company's total sales will be 14.8 billion yuan (1.78 billion US
dollars) this year, and its net profits will total 3.3 billion
yuan (397 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company, with only 28,000 employees on the payroll, has
created high production efficiency and high economic benefits
thanks to careful decision-making and strict management. Its
overall productivity per capita is expected to hit 275,000 yuan
(33,000 US dollars) this year, far higher than that of most
companies in China.
</P>
<P>
The CNOOC has reduced its asset-liability ratio to 39 percent
by repaying commercial loans in advance, Wang noted.
</P>
<P>
The company invests 1.5 billion yuan (180 million US dollars)
into risk exploration annually, with the purpose of finding more
oil and gas reserves. In this passing year of 1997, it has
verified 176 million tons of oil and 8.6 billion cu m of gas and
has achieved a success ratio of 80 percent for wildcat drilling.
</P>
<P>
Major exploration progress has been made in Pearl River
estuary, the Bohai Bay and the East China Sea, which have paved
the way for CNOOC's new round of large scale development.
</P>
<P>
The company will produce 30 million tons of oil equivalent by
the year 2005 in line with its overrun plan, Wang noted. To better
utilize oil and gas resources, CNOOC is actively developing
several downstream petrochemical projects.
</P>
<P>
Benefiting from successful foreign cooperation, CNOOC has
achieved great development since its establishment in 1982. So
far, it has drawn six billion U.S. dollars of direct foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, CNOOC has participated in four overseas projects in
Indonesia, Myanmar, Mexico and Iran.  
</P>
</TEXT>
