<HEADLINE> Spanish Government to Return Party Properties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The Spanish government
announced Friday that it would return the properties confiscated
in the 1930's during the civil war period to the former owners --
political parties and labor unions.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said this indicated that "a historical
account has been settled" on the country's democratization process.
</P>
<P>
The civil war in Spain, from 1936 to 1939, was a prelude to the
world war against Fascism in the 1930's and 1940's. The properties
of all the parties and labor unions that joined the anti-Fascism
front during the civil war were confiscated.
</P>
<P>
The settlement of the properties has been an outstanding issue
in the country since political parties were re-legalized in 1975.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Communist Party, Socialist Workers Party
and the Basque Nationalist Party will get back their confiscated
properties.
</P>
<P>
The government would establish a special property
administration to handle the confiscation issues, the spokesman
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
