<HEADLINE> Chinese Village Hires Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Huaxi, a renowned model
village in east China's Jiangsu Province, now has a dozen foreign
experts working in its factories. But village head Wu Renbao still
wants to hire more foreign experts to help them.
</P>
<P>
"We are thinking of hiring more foreign technical and
managerial personnel to meet the needs of local economic growth,"
said Wu. "We need them to help us tap the potential of our village
to the full."
</P>
<P>
As the most prosperous village in China's eastern coastal
regions, Huaxi has about 40 village-run enterprises, ten of which
are foreign-funded ventures involving in iron and steel casting,
paper making, textiles and machine-building. They have so far
hired more than 10 experts from six countries and regions
including Britain, France and the United States.
</P>
<P>
These foreign experts are on good terms with villagers and are
doing good jobs at their posts. "Comrade Peng", as local people
often call one of the two Americans experts who have been working
there since the early last year, said: "Though I have not worked
long enough here, I have already cherished profound feelings for
the village and I'm resolved to work harder still along with
villagers and build up a splendid tomorrow with them."  
</P>
