<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Take Drug Tests on Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- French officials went to the
Alpine slopes to give surprise drug tests to six soccer players on
Friday in an effort to avoid a drug scandal when the country hosts
next year's World Cup in June and July.
</P>
<P>
The testing is part of a intensified crackdown when officials
confirmed several new doping cases in October. Several players
have tested positive for steroids or illegal drug use.
</P>
<P>
The French Football Federation (FFF) at the time backed a
get-tough plan to fight doping by establishing new guidelines with
clubs, players, trainers and doctors ahead of the 1998 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The players and Coach Aime Jacquet expressed shock at the
surprise test during what they hoped would be a few days of rest
and relaxation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
