<HEADLINE> Argentine Minister Condemns Destruction of Jewish Tombs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentine Interior
Minister Carlos Corach condemned on Friday the latest desecration
and destruction of tombs and monuments at a Jewish cemetery.
</P>
<P>
Corach described the incident, occurred on Thursday night
during the celebration of Christmas Eve at the La Tablada cemetery
in the southeast of Buenos Aires province, as a "disgraceful
episode."
</P>
<P>
As it reveals the existence of a latent savagery in society, he
said, the culprits must be found and punished.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 graves and tombstones, monuments, and photographs
were defiled and destroyed by unidentified vandals.
</P>
<P>
The incident is now under investigation.
</P>
<P>
A similar incident took place at the same cemetery on the same
day of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
