<HEADLINE> United States Beat Kazakhstan in Junior Ice Hockey Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The United States defeated
Kazakhstan 8-2 in a group B match at the World Junior Ice Hockey
Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
But defending champion Canada lost for the second night in a
row as Sweden won 4-0 behind 22 saves from goaltender Johan
Holmqvist as the Swedes outshot Canada 35-22 in Group A.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Finland crushed Germany 5-0 and Switzerland
upended Slovakia 3-1 in Hameenlinna.
</P>
<P>
Finland, who beat Canada on Thursday, leads the group A with a
perfect 2-0 record. The Czech Republic is 1-0, Sweden 1-1, Germany
0-1 and Canada 0-2.
</P>
<P>
In Group B, Russia and Switzerland are 1-0, the United States
and Slovakia are 1-1 and Kazakhstan at 0-2. 
