<HEADLINE> Spain to Destroy All Anti-Personnel Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain plans to destroy all of
its anti-personnel land mines within three years, the government
said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government pledged, in a decree, for a total ban on the
production, export and use of anti-personnel land mines.
</P>
<P>
At a cabinet session the same day, the government approved the
allocation of 3 million U.S. dollars to destory the country's
stockpile of 800,000 land mines. 
</P>
