<HEADLINE> Maxi Brindabella Regains Hobart Race Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Australian maxi Brindabella
regained the lead from Swedish challenger Nicorette in the 53rd
Sydney-to-Hobart race on Saturday as strong southerly winds forced
six yachts to retire overnight.
</P>
<P>
George Snow's 23-meter Brindabella had been the first yacht out
of Sydney Harbour on the 630 nautical mile race and overtook
Nicorette at about 3.00 a.m. local time (1600 GMT) as the
108-strong fleet beat into southerly winds of up to 30 knots and
heavy seas.
</P>
<P>
The six yachts to retire overnight from the starting fleet of
115 were all Australian entries.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney-to-Hobart is one of the world's leading three ocean
races, along with England's Fastnet and the United States' Newport
to Bermuda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
