<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Spends Christmas Full of Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 26 (Xinhua) -- In France, this year's Christmas
was marked by a series of accidents, some of them very bizarre,
according to local media reports.
</P>
<P>
A 61-year-old woman was devoured by 10 dogs in a small town
called Chanteheux in Meurthe-et-Moselle, eastern France, said
police. The body of Micheline Brindel was discovered by her
husband in her sleeping room this evening.
</P>
<P>
A 19-year-old girl riding a motorcycle was killed by a running
train on a railtrack in Albertville, Savoie in eastern France.
Emilie Louvet died instantly after bumping with the train which
threw her to a wall nearby, said reports.
</P>
<P>
A woman falsely accused an employee of a record library in
Avignon, southern France, of raping, because the man, who played
Santa Claus during the Christmas, ordered her out of the shop for
her drunkenness the day before.
</P>
<P>
The unidentified 32-year-old woman reported to police at four
o'clock this morning that she was raped in a restroom by a Santa
Claus, but several witnesses and a doctor's report countered her
statement before she was forced to withdraw the accusation.
</P>
<P>
The traffic of buses in the southcentral city of Dijon came to
a standstill today after a bus driver was beaten with baseball bat
by a man who came up to his bus. The unions appealed for a strike
to protest the attack.
</P>
<P>
A 23-year-old man was arrested today after biting a policeman
and kicking several others in Strasbourg. The accident took place
after Ismail Kaoulal quarrelled with police who blamed him for not
parking his car the right way.
</P>
<P>
A man who tried to commit suicide with gas severely burned
himself and put his house in flame in Belfort in eastern France
Thursday night. Explosion was heard from the garage of the victim
who was staying in his car with gas bottles and had kept the motor
running.
</P>
<P>
A man was found lying dead on a road in Dordogne, southwest
France. Police said he was apparently crushed by a car which had
fled afterwards, said reports.
</P>
<P>
A dozen vehicles were burnt down by unknown people on the
Christmas eve on Wednesday and today in Strasbourg, reports quoted
police as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
