<DOCNO> XIE19971227.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.Y. Stocks Edge Higher in Light Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 26 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks edged higher
in the year's lightest trading Friday, as Dow Jones industrial
average rose 19.18 points to 7,679.31 by the 1 p.m. close.
</P>
<P>
The Dow trimmed the week's loss to 79.98, pushing this year's
gain back above 19 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq market managed a sizable gain amid some
bargain-hunting in the battered technology group. The Nasdaq index
rose 11.85 points to 1,511.38, led by Microsoft and Cisco Systems.
</P>
<P>
Only 154.84 million shares changed hands on the New York Stock
Exchange, the lightest session for the whole year and down
substantially from the 263.33 million shares traded Christmas Eve,
when stock trading also was shortened.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 6-to-5 margin on
the NYSE. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 3.76 to
936.46, and the NYSE composite index rose 1.28 to 493.60.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.45 to 421.49,
and the small-company dominated American Stock Exchange composite
index rose 1.17 to 663.77.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
